Self-acclaimed Yoruba freedom fighter, Sunday Adeyemo, popularly known as Sunday Igboho, has distanced himself from a company registered in his name in the United Kingdom. Igboho's media aide, Olayomi Koiki, who raised the disclaimer on Sunday, said Igboho was not informed about the existence of the company identified as Chief Sunday Adeyemo Igboho Diaspora Supporters Group. Igboho Koiki also said Igboho's consent was not taken before the formation of the company on February 12, 2021. He wrote, “This is to inform the general public that Chief Sunday Igboho is not aware and his consent was not taken before a limited company was registered in the UK on the 12th of February 2021 with the following details Chief Sunday Adeyemo Igboho Diaspora Supporters Group with Company Number 13199001. Director: Badejo Omorinola Maureen. Secretary: Oba Yomi Olaposi Olayomi.” The organisation's details as stated on Companies House Service show the director of the company is Badejo Omorinola Maureen while the Secretary is Oba Yomi Olaposi Olayomi. The nature of the business was described as “activities of extraterritorial organisations and bodies.”